Description :

Premium Markets is an automated stock market analysis system.
It implements a graphical environment for monitoring stock market technical analysis
major indicators, portfolio management and historical data charting.
Please refer to Premium Markets PRICE TREND FORECAST web portal at 
http://premiummarkets.elasticbeanstalk.com/ 
for a preview and a free workable demo of the trend prediction feature.

How to install?

Premium Markets is java based and requires version 6 or later. Please, check that you 
have an up to date version of java at http://www.java.com/ installed before hand.

Premium markets is available 
at http://sourceforge.net/projects/pmsqueak/files/latest/download?source=files for a 
direct installation using jnlp technology.
If java is properly enabled for you web browser, you should then be prompted to open 
the above link using "Java Web Launcher". If it doesn't happens or it opens the jnlp 
file with another application, you will have to select the "Java Web Launcher", "javaw" 
or "Java Web Start" in the "Other applications" drop down list offered by your browser.

If this is not compliant with your operating system and its settings, you can also 
try downloading the installation jar at http://sourceforge.net/projects/pmsqueak/files/pm.jar
Then double click on the downloaded jar in your file explorer,
Or open a command terminal, cd to the download folder and issue the following command : 
java -jar pm.jar

Requirements :
This application is based on the Java Runtime Environment (JRE) 6.0 or newer
It should come installed on your system by default.
See http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp for more details.
This application also requires a compliant version of SWT libraries with your OS
The most common are included in this package.
See http://www.eclipse.org/swt/ 

